    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A technique, usually in watercolor, in which the design is derived from an accidental mark or blot. This technique was originally described by the watercolor painter Alexander Couzens in 1786.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046691/Lucie-Smith, Thames &amp; Hudson Dictionary of Art Terms (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Técnica utilizada habitualmente en acuarela en la cual el dibujo es derivado a partir de una marca o mancha accidental.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een techniek, meestal een waterverftechniek, waarbij het getekende of geschilderde patroon is ontstaan uit een per ongeluk aangebrachte streep of vlek. Deze techniek is oorspronkelijk in 1786 beschreven door de waterverfschilder Alexander Couzens.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>將水彩等顏料潑濺於紙上，以顏料隨機形成之標記或漬跡設計作畫的技術。此種技術最早於西元1786年由水彩畫家亞歷山大．卡曾斯（Alexander Couzens）述及。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
